How to create a custom component in Dynamics:
To initialize your custom pcf contol project follow this microsoft guide:
Create and build a code component - Power Apps | Microsoft Learn 
https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/power-apps/developer/component-framework/create-custom-controls-using-pcf

To begin building your control use this example guide for understanding:
Create your first component using Power Apps Component Framework in Microsoft Dataverse - Power Apps | Microsoft Learn 
https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/power-apps/developer/component-framework/implementing-controls-using-typescript?tabs=after#add-type-group-element

To debug the UI without uploading to dynamics use this guide:
Debug code components - Power Apps | Microsoft Learn 
https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/power-apps/developer/component-framework/debugging-custom-controls

Relevant pac commands:
Microsoft Power Platform CLI solution command group - Power Platform | Microsoft Learn 
https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/power-platform/developer/cli/reference/solution#pac-solution-init

Deploy af PCF
Opret solution (pac solution init -pn "KL" -pp "kl")

Tilføj ref til PCF (pac solution add-reference --path ./..)

Ændre proj file med Both i PropertyGroup

Byg i release (dotnet build -c Release)

Import til dev (pac solution import --path ./bin/Release/solution.zip -f -pc)

The publisher name and prefix for KL is the following:
pac solution init --publisher-name kemplauritzenas --publisher-prefix kl

So the usual flow:

Make TypeScript changes → npm run build (success)
Build the solution → dotnet build <your>.cdsproj to generate updated solution package (.zip)
Import that .zip into Dynamics to see the changes live.
So, every time you update your PCF control for import:

Update the control.manifest.xml version (e.g., 1.0.1).
Update the package.json version to match (1.0.1).
Clean & rebuild the project.
